<br>
With the whole guild holding back for him (not an enforced rule, just something we were all doing to help him) it was getting frustrating so Tarin defaulted the scale to him in the next raid.  This was advertised as such on the Battlefield Forum before the raid so that all attendees were aware of the fact.  We also are painfully aware that for the most part the rest of the stuff that drops isn't too great so we donated &quot;loot&quot;.... which consisted of, amongst other things, Blue Diamond Bracelets and a bunch of stuff for the Earring of Solstice Quest.  This worked well.  No one got upset as everyone knew what the deal was.  <br>
<br>
I think to default something to one specific player at the end of a raid without mention of it beforehand is wrong.  Even if it wasn't officially defaulted and was more of a &quot;it's only right&quot;.  It may well be the right thing to do, and I don't question that Suometer deserved the drop as running open raids is, from what I hear, a nightmare, however, it should have been decided before the raid... not after.  <br>
<br>
