<br>
I was on this raid last night, and at no time did I see on raid channel pressure to not roll on the book. Suometar called for the roll as she promised.  I know I was very careful not to do anything in /ts either, for Suometar is very very scrupulous on the fairness of her raids. I cannot of course speak for all the raid members here.<br>
<br>
Both Timwin and Suometar rolled, and after a pause Suometar was declared the winner with the higher roll. I admit we were all very glad for her, and I personally made a vow that I would lead dragon raids until every other paladin on that raid got a book - because I was so impressed that folk would act in the selfless way that I saw!  Actually if you read the log of the text I sent to Valquiss I was happily saying that I would lead until all shamen got books, but this represented a personal over-multitasking confusion and does not really apply LOL &lt;Valquiss knew what I meant! &gt;  I repeated this statement to several who can confirm it.<br>
<br>
